main event: The report describes the sighting of a star-like object moving from the northeast to the southwest at high speed and an altitude of around 20,000 feet, observed visually and on radar by a naval unit in the northern latitudes.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 75 seconds before disappearing.
The object was described as having a magnitude of 0, indicating it was bright.
The object maintained a constant altitude during the sighting.
Other naval units in the area also reported observing a fast-moving unidentified object at the same time.
The report concludes that the object could have been a satellite, meteor, balloon, or aircraft, but there was insufficient information to make a definitive evaluation.
sighted object: a bright, star-like object moving rapidly through the sky
